# [ACE](../wg/ace.html)

## Summary

The ACE (Authentication and Authorization for Constrained Environments) working group met at IETF 125 to discuss the status of its active drafts. The session included an update on the transition of Area Directors (AD), with Paul Wouters stepping down and Chris Lemmons taking over the role. The group reviewed progress on several key profiles, including the EST-OSCORE profile, the CoAP Pub-Sub profile, the Workflow and Parameters draft, and the EDHOC-OSCORE profile. Significant technical discussions focused on certificate handling in EST, error recovery in Short Distribution Chain (SDC) workflows, and nonce derivation when combining EDHOC with other ACE profiles.

