### 2. Protecting EST Payloads with OSCORE
**Presenter:** Mališa Vučinić
**Draft:** [draft-ietf-ace-coap-est-oscore](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ace-draft-ietf-ace-coap-est-oscore-10)
**Slides:** [draft-ietf-ace-coap-est-oscore-10](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ace-draft-ietf-ace-coap-est-oscore-10-00)

*   **Status:** Working Group Last Call (WGLC) concluded. Recent updates addressed reviews from Marco Tiloca and Esko Dijk.
*   **Resolved Issues:**
    *   **Issue 113 (Certificate Bag vs. Chain):** Based on feedback from Esko Dijk, the document now mandates support for a "bag" of certificates rather than an explicit chain. A bag is more general and allows for rekeying CA certificates after deployment.
    *   **Certificate References:** Clarified that mixing X509 (X5U) and CBOR-encoded (C5U) references in the same multipart report is not supported due to ambiguity in application types. Only CBOR-encoded references are supported by this specification.
*   **Conclusion:** The authors believe the draft is ready for submission to the IESG.

### 3. CoAP Pub-Sub Profile for ACE
**Presenter:** Marco Tiloca
**Draft:** [draft-ietf-ace-coap-pubsub-profile](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ace-coap-pubsub-profile-03)
**Slides:** [draft-ietf-ace-coap-pubsub-profile](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ace-draft-ietf-ace-coap-pubsub-profile-00)

*   **Status:** Post-WGLC. Version 03 aligns the document with comments received during the IETF Last Call of other application profiles (e.g., `draft-ietf-ace-key-group-oscore-profile`).
*   **Technical Updates:**
    *   **Proof of Possession (PoP):** Added explicit text clarifying that PoP refers to the private key of the prover.
    *   **Rejoining Optimization:** Introduced a sentinel value (null or byte string) to allow clients to rejoin a group without re-providing authentication credentials if they are already known to the Key Distribution Center (KDC).
    *   **Operational Considerations:** Added a new section on logging requirements at the KDC, specifically regarding error events and privacy-sensitive information redaction.
*   **Discussion:** The draft has a normative dependency on `draft-ietf-core-coap-pubsub`. The chairs and authors agreed to wait for the CORE draft to progress further before submitting this profile to the IESG.

### 4. Short Distribution Chain (SDC) Workflow and New OAuth Parameters
**Presenter:** Marco Tiloca
**Draft:** [draft-ietf-ace-workflow-and-params](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ace-draft-ietf-ace-workflow-and-params-00)
**Slides:** [draft-ietf-ace-workflow-and-params](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ace-draft-ietf-ace-workflow-and-params-00)

*   **Status:** Active Working Group document.
*   **Workflow Improvements:**
    *   Addressed a corner case where the Authorization Server (AS) fails to upload a token to the Resource Server (RS) during a dynamic update.
    *   **Proposed Recovery:** If the upload fails because the RS deleted the token series (e.g., due to memory constraints), the AS can automatically start a new token series and attempt a fresh upload, assuming no client-specific parameters prevent it.
*   **Discussion:** Dave Thaler suggested moving text related to token series updates into a separate section (now Section 3.7) to improve readability. Dave Thaler also flagged potential confusion regarding the `rs_cnf` parameter's "must not" vs. "should not" requirements when a client lacks RS credentials.
*   **AD Note:** Chris Lemmons (incoming AD) commented that the "Operational Considerations" section should only be included if there is meaningful content to add; boilerplate "nothing to say" sections are discouraged.

### 5. EDHOC and OSCORE Profile for ACE
**Presenter:** Rikard Höglund
**Draft:** [draft-ietf-ace-edhoc-oscore-profile](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ace-edhoc-oscore-profile-10)
**Slides:** [EDHOC and OSCORE ACE profile slides IETF 125](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ace-edhoc-and-oscore-ace-profile-slides-ietf-125-00)

*   **Status:** Version 10 released.
*   **Technical Updates:**
    *   **Simplification:** Removed four unnecessary parameters (max message size, content format, endpoint ID types, transport) from the EDHOC Information Object.
    *   **Nonce (`N_S`) Derivation:** Defined a method to derive the nonce (`N_S`) using the EDHOC exporter. This is necessary when using this profile with other profiles (like Key Group or Pub-Sub) because the client might not interact with the RS `authz-info` endpoint where nonces are typically provided.
*   **Early Allocation:** The authors requested early IANA allocation for confirmation method registries (CWT/AWT) and the EDHOC External Authorization Data (EAD) registry to facilitate implementation.

